    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Upon reaching 17th level, you are no longer required to maintain concentration (as if you were concentrating on a spell) to maintain your illusory duplicates from Channel Divinity: Invoke Duplicity. As a bonus action, while you are concentrating on a spell, you can move the point of origin to one of your duplicates, but you are the source of concentration for the spell. If the illusory duplicate is the source of such a spell and it would take damage, you must succeed a DC 10 Concentration check to maintain concentration.</p>",
